TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {22091=2013|Stats : Made an immediate impact as a freshman, starting 15 of 17 games in the midfield…made her first career start in the team’s season-opener at Quinnipiac…named to the Ivy League Weekly Honor Roll on September 30 after tallying her first career goal in the Bears’ 2-1 victory at UMass…recorded a total of 13 shots on the season, including six on goal. Before Brown: A four-year starter on the soccer team at Winnacunnet High School, Carly also played basketball for four years and ran track for one season … Was also the starting kicker for the Winnacunnet football team as a senior … Was a First Team All-State selection in soccer as a junior and a senior, earning team MVP honors both of those seasons … Captained both the basketball and soccer teams as a senior, earning MVP honors in basketball her senior year … Helped to lead the basketball team to the Division I State Championship in both 2010 and 2011 … Named Second Team All-State in basketball … Also an Honorable Mention All-State honoree as the kicker for the football team, helping to lead Winnacunnet to the Division II State Championship in 2012 … Played club soccer for Seacoast United … High Honor Roll student throughout high school … Personal: The daughter of Jay and Katherine Gould, Carly has two brothers, Jesse and Jon … Also enjoys paddle boarding, skiing, yoga and hiking … Undecided on a concentration., 62429=Brown University Athletics | 235 Hope St. Box 1932 | Providence, RI 02912, 25133=2013}
